Mini Snake Game

A classic Snake game built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, rendered with PixiJS.  
This is a frontend-only project that runs entirely in the browser with no backend or build step.


Features

- Grid-based Snake movement
- Smooth rendering using PixiJS
- Multiple fruit types (Apple, Banana, Orange)
- Score tracking
- Play / Restart button
- Keyboard controls (Arrow keys)
- Sound effects using the Web Audio API
- Game Over overlay screen

Tech Stack

- HTML – Structure
- CSS – Styling
- JavaScript – Game logic
- PixiJS (v7) – 2D rendering (loaded via CDN)
- Web Audio API – Sound effects


Project Structure

mini-snake-game/
│── index.html          # Main HTML file
│── script.js           # Game logic
│── Makefile            # Command to run the project
│── README.md


How to Run the Game

Option 1: Open directly

Open `index.html` in any modern browser.

> Works fine for this project since it does not use backend APIs.

Option 2: Using Makefile (recommended)

```bash
make run
